article.headline: Army 70, Bucknell 53
article.story: LEWISBURG, Pa. -- Julian Simmons scored 21 points and Josh Miller had 18 as Army beat Bucknell 70-53 on Saturday. Doug Williams added 14 points and Richard Cleveland chipped in 12 for Army (10-18, 6-8 Patriot League). Patrick Behan had 23 points and 12 rebounds for Bucknell (7-22, 4-10), while Justin Castleberry scored 11 points and Darryl Shazier added nine. Army held a 29-27 edge at the half but began the second period with a 19-2 run capped by back-to-back 3-pointers by Simmons to take a 48-29 lead with 14:37 remaining.
